SIMPLE: bunchy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bunchy
<hw>Bunch"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Swelling
out in bunches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An unshapen, <qex>bunchy</qex> spear, with bark unpiled.</q>
<rj><qau>Phaer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Growing in bunches, or resembling a bunch; having
tufts; <as>as, the bird's <ex>bunchy</ex> tail</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>Yielding irregularly; sometimes
rich, sometimes poor; <as>as, a <ex>bunchy</ex> mine</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Page.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bunco</ent>⟦br⟧
